== English ==
===Noun===

'''dead donkey''' (plural:dead donkeys)

In [[journalism|journalistic]] jargon, a [[news]] item of no real significance, usually of whimsical or sentimental nature, placed at the end of a news bulletin or in a [[newspaper]] as filler. A dead donkey can often be removed from the programme or publication if a more significant story needs extra time or space.

The title of the British [[sitcom]] ''Drop the Dead Donkey'' refers to this term. ''see'' [[Wikipedia:Drop the Dead Donkey|Wikipedia entry]].